
[1]sumptuary

   SUMP'TUARY, a. [L. sumptuarius, from sumptus, expense.]

   Relating to expense. Sumptuary laws or regulations are such as restrain
   or limit the expenses of citizens in apparel, food, furniture, &c.
   Sumptuary laws are abridgments of liberty, and of very difficult
   execution. They can be justified only on the ground of extreme
   necessity.
